This was a feature film I did called, Love & a .45 w/ Rene Zellweger, Peter Fonda, Rory Cochrane and Gil Bellows- directed by C.M. Talkington shot in Austin, TX. I remember fighting desperately for a chance to audition for the role of Mary Ann because “the biz” seemed to have preconceived ideas of what I could/ couldn’t play from my prior roles and, honestly, I’ve always thought of myself as a character actor and deeply want to play roles where I can be challenged and disappear into. For me, it’s not the size of the role but rather the writing, cast, director and the layered depth of a character that I can try my best to sink my teeth into. I remember how much I loved working with this cast and learning as much I could about what it must feel like to be high on heroine- talked to former addicts, etc and when we filmed this scene, I sniffed vitamin B- 12 off of a large knife to try and simulate the burning feel of doing speed like drugs (not something I would recommend!!). My dream is to play more roles where I’m unrecognizable and pushed outside my comfort zone, like this one as it was soo damn fun #actortalkwithCharlotte

Giorgio was my first friend when I moved to LA (from Chicago) to be a singer (and an actress). We were working together on a couple of albums (released 1 in Germany). He is an icon in the music industry, 3 Oscars for the soundtracks of Midnight Express, Top Gun and Flashdance but also did the soundtracks of Scarface, American Gigolo, etc and is deemed by many as the “king of disco” w/ Donna Summer- has countless awards/ Grammys, etc but, it’s our decades long friendship that I cherish most… 🙏🏼Remember to value life long friends— a blessing for sure ❤️

Maybe we will be working together again one day…😉 🎤 #giogiomoroder

Comedy… I LOVE doing comedy🤪 This was a series I did w/ @paulyshore @kevinweisman created by the amazing @zimmermanstan & @jb_sees for the Fox Network called PAULY👏🏻 Although the series only went one season, I had a blast shooting it as it was almost like Saturday Night Live w/ a sketch comedy vibe sometimes 😝 I think doing live audience sit-coms are soo exciting because you can really feel when a joke is working (or not☺️). The black and white “nightmare scene” is a take off of Faye Dunaway (Joan Crawford) in Mommie Dearest- just FYI 🎬Shout out to our sweet, talented costume designer, Kevin King (who is no longer with us 🙏🏼) and my brilliant hairdresser @kentnscott who is doing my hair for my upcoming project (being released in 2024) 🤫 😉 This episode was directed by the amazing @mandyblvd #actortalkwithcharlotte #mommiedearest

This scene from the series, NYPD BLUE is one I will never forget… ☺️The young son of my fiancé (played by the extraordinary Dennis Franz) walks in on me in the bathroom. The scene took all day to film as we had to line up his ears, angles thru my legs, etc. But, the scene went on to cause a lot of…controversy. The FCC stated that, “Charlotte’s buttocks are titillating and shocking” and successfully sued ABC 1.4 mil for the racy scene. Then it escalated to the 2nd U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals which struck down the FCC indecent policy claiming that it “violated the First Amendment because it’s unconstitutionally vague.” Seems the argument was based on the idea that “buttocks” are indeed a “sexual organ”. Who would’ve ever thought my ass would be debated as “decent” or “indecent” in the courts… 😳 #nypdblue

Been singing in the recording studio for a while now & will be releasing a few songs as soon as we finish filming our music video- I hope you’ll want to hear/ see it! 🙏🏼🎤For those who do not know, I moved to La-La Land to become a singer-I released a few albums here and in Europe and have a gold record 🤷‍♀️ from singing in a TV series called, The Heights but… my acting career kept me soo busy, I had to chose (said the record labels). I love singing- write most of my music and can’t wait to release them… HOPING you’ll want to listen! 🙏🏼☺️ #singer #singing #recordingstudio #giorgiomoroder

Fostering saves lives and it has brought me soo much joy! If you’ve never fostered before, please consider it!🙏🏼 It can be as little as a few days or even months but it helps the animal(s) feel safe and learn consistent love which in turn makes them more adoptable. Please, think about going to your local county or city animal shelter and fill your home with love while helping save innocent lives❤️🐶🐱 #foster #fosteringsaveslives #fostercare #fosterdog #fosterkittens #adoptdontshop #dogs #cats
